alert.note: Alert for Interstate 5 Corridor; Western Antelope Valley Foothills (California) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Wind Advisory issued September 26 at 2:15PM PDT until September 28 at 5:00AM PDT by NWS Oxnard
info.description: ...WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM PDT THURSDAY... * WHAT...Northwest winds 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to 55 mph. * WHERE...Interstate 5 Corridor and Western Antelope Valley Foothills. * WHEN...Until 5 AM PDT Thursday. * IMPACTS...Gusty winds will blow around unsecured objects and make driving difficult, especially for high profile vehicles. Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may result. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...These strong winds will combine with a dry air mass to create elevated fire weather conditions.
info.instruction: Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.
